article.headline: Dartmouth 37, Columbia 28
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Hudson Smythe scored three times, including one touchdown with less than 2 minutes to go, to lead Dartmouth to a 38-27 back-and-forth win over Columbia on Saturday. Two runners, Nate Servis and Rob Mitchelson, each gained more than 100 yards for Dartmouth -- the first time that's happened in 45 years. Columbia (1-5) scored first in front of the Dartmouth Homecoming crowd, as Austin Knowlin took a 16-yard pass from Craig Hormann early in the first quarter. Dartmouth (2-4) answered with a 1-yard run by Smythe and a 18-yard touchdown pass from fullback Julian Collins to Phil Galligan. Columbia tied the game at 14 late in the half on a 32-yard reception by Nico Gutierrez, but Dartmouth scored less than 3 minutes later on a 11-yard reception by Brian Evans. Columbia came back in the third quarter with a 40-yard touchdown pass from Hormann to Taylor Joseph, but Dartmouth took the lead again on Smythe's second scoring run, from three yards out. Columbia's final touchdown -- a 27-yard run by Knowlin- tied the game again at 28 before Smythe's 2-yard run and a safety by Andrew Dete.
